data.description: Excellent location for this ranch style home located on a cul-de-sac lot in the quiet Old Farm neighborhood of Starwatch. Well maintained, light and bright home w/vaulted ceilings and an open main level great for entertaining family and friends. Central air and heat for year-round comfort.  Attractive wood laminate floors through the Living Rm and hallway. All window blinds, drapes, and rods stay. The Entry has a tile floor and coat closet for guests. It leads you into the Living Room that warms you w/a wood burning fireplace and brick surround to cozy up on winter nights. The Kitchen offers a tile floor and walk out Dining Area to the backyard deck. The Kitchen features a garden window, pantry, counter bar, and ample cabinets & counter space for storage and food preparation. Appliances include a range oven, vent hood, Bosch dishwasher, French door refrigerator, & Jenn Air counter grill & counter microwave. Convenient garage access from the hallway. Double doors lead you into the Private Owner’s Suite that boasts a walk out to the backyard deck, and an adjoining Bathroom. The Bathroom offers a walk-in closet, a skylight, vanity, mirror, and tiled shower. BR#2 is adjacent to the Hall Shower Bathroom w/vanity, mirror, and tiled shower w/built-in seat. The Finished Basement boasts an expansive Family Room with a wood-burning fireplace and a pool table that stays. 2 more BRs on this level share a convenient 3/4-bathroom w/large shower. 2-car attached garage w/door opener & storage. The fenced backyard offers a large deck for outdoor dining and relaxation. Large natural boulders enhance a corner of the backyard and are part of the unique character of the neighborhood. This delightful home is located close to schools, shopping, and the Powers Corridor. Parks and trails are just minutes away. It’s an easy commute to Fort Carson or the Peterson Space Force Base. This delightful home offers style, comfort, and convenience, making it an ideal choice for your next home.
